<p>
<seg id=1> US President Clinton made a pledge on AIDS day to provide new assistance for the prevention of the fatal disease, including the allocation of more governmental loans. </seg>
<seg id=2> Clinton planned to increase funding for the National Health Institute for the research of AIDS by 30%. </seg>
<seg id=3> He is also preparing to announce the provision of US$10 million for the care of orphans suffering from AIDS. </seg>
<seg id=4> The Clinton government said that after the provision the research fund will be the biggest investment of American public funds in AIDS research. </seg>
</p>
